   "source": [
    "# BB84 Quantum Key Distribution Simulation\n",
    "\n",
    "## Overview\n",
    "This notebook implements a simulation of the BB84 quantum key distribution protocol, which allows two parties (Alice and Bob) to establish a secure cryptographic key using quantum mechanics principles.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Theory\n",
    "- **+ basis**: 0° and 90° polarization\n",
    "- **× basis**: 45° and -45° polarization\n",
    "- Security relies on quantum uncertainty and disturbance during measurement (no-cloning theorem)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Imports and Setup"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from numpy import random\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from scipy.stats import norm, binom\n",
    "import time\n",
    "\n",
    "# Configure plotting\n",
    "plt.rcParams['axes.prop_cycle'] = plt.cycler(color=['#d6466d', '#5bc760', '#2862de'])\n",
    "%matplotlib inline"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. BB84 Protocol Without Eavesdropper"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2.1 Random Bit and Basis Generation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def random_without_eve(length):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Generate random bits for Alice and random bases for both Alice and Bob.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Parameters:\n",
    "    length (int): Number of bits to generate\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "    tuple: (alice_bits, alice_bases, bob_bases)\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    alice_bit = random.randint(2, size=length)\n",
    "    alice_base = ['+' if i == 0 else 'x' for i in random.randint(2, size=length)]\n",
    "    bob_base = ['+' if i == 0 else 'x' for i in random.randint(2, size=length)]\n",
    "    return alice_bit, alice_base, bob_base"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2.2 Quantum Channel Simulation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def simulation_without_eve(alice_base, alice_bit, bob_base):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Simulate quantum transmission without eavesdropper.\n",
    "    Bob only gets correct bits when measurement bases match Alice's preparation bases.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Parameters:\n",
    "    alice_base (list): Alice's basis choices\n",
    "    alice_bit (list): Alice's bit values\n",
    "    bob_base (list): Bob's measurement bases\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "    list: Bob's measured bits\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    bob_bit = []\n",
    "    for i in range(len(alice_bit)):\n",
    "        if alice_base[i] == bob_base[i]:\n",
    "            bob_bit.append(alice_bit[i])\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            bob_bit.append(random.randint(2))\n",
    "    return bob_bit"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. BB84 Protocol With Eavesdropper (Eve)\n",
    "\n",
    "In this version of the BB84 protocol, an eavesdropper (Eve) intercepts the qubits sent by Alice, measures them using a random basis, and then retransmits them to Bob. This process can introduce detectable errors in the final key."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def random_with_eve(length):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Generate random bits and bases including Eve's interception.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Parameters:\n",
    "    length (int): Number of bits to generate\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "    tuple: (alice_bits, alice_bases, bob_bases, eve_intercept_bases, eve_retransmit_bases)\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    alice_bit = random.randint(2, size=length)\n",
    "    alice_base = ['+' if i == 0 else 'x' for i in random.randint(2, size=length)]\n",
    "    bob_base = ['+' if i == 0 else 'x' for i in random.randint(2, size=length)]\n",
    "    eve_base_inc = ['+' if i == 0 else 'x' for i in random.randint(2, size=length)]\n",
    "    eve_base_tran = eve_base_inc.copy()  # Eve retransmits in same basis\n",
    "    return alice_bit, alice_base, bob_base, eve_base_inc, eve_base_tran"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def simulation_with_eve(alice_base, alice_bit, bob_base, eve_base_inc, eve_base_tran):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Simulate quantum transmission with eavesdropper Eve intercepting and retransmitting.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Parameters:\n",
    "    alice_base (list): Alice's basis choices\n",
    "    alice_bit (list): Alice's bit values\n",
    "    bob_base (list): Bob's measurement bases\n",
    "    eve_base_inc (list): Eve's interception bases\n",
    "    eve_base_tran (list): Eve's retransmission bases\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "    tuple: (bob_bits, eve_bits)\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    bob_bit, eve_bit = [], []\n",
    "    n = len(alice_bit)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Eve intercepts and measures\n",
    "    for i in range(n):\n",
    "        if alice_base[i] == eve_base_inc[i]:\n",
    "            eve_bit.append(alice_bit[i])\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            eve_bit.append(random.randint(2))\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Eve retransmits to Bob\n",
    "    for j in range(n):\n",
    "        if eve_base_tran[j] == bob_base[j]:\n",
    "            bob_bit.append(eve_bit[j])\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            bob_bit.append(random.randint(2))\n",
    "\n",
    "    return bob_bit, eve_bit"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Key Generation and Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "Here the secure key is generated by matching the bits when both Bob and Alice used the same basis. This would be discussed openly via classical communication.\n",
    "The QBER is calculated by dividing the number of bits within the key that do NOT match by the total key length. If this number is above a certain tolerance then we can confidently state that Eve was present. for BB84 protocol, we expect a QBER of around 25% when Eve is intercepting."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def create_key(alice_base, alice_bits, bob_base, bob_bits):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Create final key by sifting bases and comparing bits.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Parameters:\n",
    "    alice_base (list): Alice's basis choices\n",
    "    alice_bits (list): Alice's bit values\n",
    "    bob_base (list): Bob's basis choices\n",
    "    bob_bits (list): Bob's measured bits\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "    list: [final_key, key_length, matched_bases_count, correct_bits, error_bits, accuracy]\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    n = len(alice_base)\n",
    "    matched_base = [None]*n\n",
    "    matched_bits = [None]*n\n",
    "    count_true = count_false = 0\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Identify matching bases\n",
    "    for i in range(n):\n",
    "        if alice_base[i] == bob_base[i]:\n",
    "            matched_base[i] = alice_base[i]\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Compare bits in matching bases\n",
    "    for i in range(n):\n",
    "        if matched_base[i] is not None:\n",
    "            if alice_bits[i] == bob_bits[i]:\n",
    "                matched_bits[i] = True\n",
    "                count_true += 1\n",
    "            else:\n",
    "                matched_bits[i] = False\n",
    "                count_false += 1\n",
    "\n",
    "    total_count = count_true + count_false\n",
    "    accuracy = count_true / n if n > 0 else 0\n",
    "    res_key = [bob_bits[i] for i in range(n) if matched_base[i] is not None]\n",
    "    return [res_key, len(res_key), total_count, count_true, count_false, accuracy]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def print_stats(alice_base, bob_base, alice_bits, bob_bits):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Print detailed statistics of the quantum key distribution.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Parameters:\n",
    "    alice_base (list): Alice's basis choices\n",
    "    bob_base (list): Bob's basis choices\n",
    "    alice_bits (list): Alice's bit values\n",
    "    bob_bits (list): Bob's measured bits\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    n = len(alice_bits)\n",
    "    matched_base = [None]*n\n",
    "    count_true = count_false = 0\n",
    "\n",
    "    for i in range(n):\n",
    "        if alice_base[i] == bob_base[i]:\n",
    "            matched_base[i] = alice_base[i]\n",
    "\n",
    "    for i in range(n):\n",
    "        if matched_base[i] is not None:\n",
    "            if alice_bits[i] == bob_bits[i]:\n",
    "                count_true += 1\n",
    "            else:\n",
    "                count_false += 1\n",
    "\n",
    "    total_count = count_true + count_false\n",
    "    accuracy = count_true / n\n",
    "    QBER = count_false / total_count if total_count > 0 else 0\n",
    "\n",
    "    print(f'Accuracy: {accuracy:.6f}')\n",
    "    print('Total bits sent by Alice:', n)\n",
    "    print('Matching bases:', total_count)\n",
    "    print('Mismatched bits:', count_false)\n",
    "    print('Matching bits:', count_true)\n",
    "    print(f'QBER (Quantum Bit Error Rate): {QBER:.6f}')\n",
    "    print('---')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Encryption and Message Transmission"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def string_to_binary(string):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Convert string to list of binary bits.\"\"\"\n",
    "    binary_list = []\n",
    "    for char in string:\n",
    "        bin_char = format(ord(char), '08b')\n",
    "        for bit in bin_char:\n",
    "            binary_list.append(int(bit))\n",
    "    return binary_list\n",
    "\n",
    "def binary_to_string(binary_list):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Convert list of binary bits back to string.\"\"\"\n",
    "    chars = []\n",
    "    for i in range(0, len(binary_list), 8):\n",
    "        chunk = binary_list[i:i+8]\n",
    "        char_int = int(''.join(map(str, chunk)), 2)\n",
    "        chars.append(chr(char_int))\n",
    "    return ''.join(chars)\n",
    "\n",
    "def encryption(data, key):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Encrypt data using XOR with key.\"\"\"\n",
    "    if len(data) != len(key):\n",
    "        key = key[:len(data)]  # Truncate key if longer than data\n",
    "    return [data[i] ^ key[i] for i in range(len(data))]\n",
    "\n",
    "def decryption(message, key):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Decrypt message using XOR with key (same as encryption).\"\"\"\n",
    "    return encryption(message, key)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Monte Carlo QBER Analysis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def compute_qber(alice_base, bob_base, alice_bits, bob_bits):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Compute Quantum Bit Error Rate (QBER).\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Parameters:\n",
    "    alice_base (list): Alice's basis choices\n",
    "    bob_base (list): Bob's basis choices\n",
    "    alice_bits (list): Alice's bit values\n",
    "    bob_bits (list): Bob's measured bits\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "    float: QBER value\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    matched_indices = [i for i in range(len(alice_base)) if alice_base[i] == bob_base[i]]\n",
    "    if len(matched_indices) == 0:\n",
    "        return 0\n",
    "    errors = sum(alice_bits[i] != bob_bits[i] for i in matched_indices)\n",
    "    qber = errors / len(matched_indices)\n",
    "    return qber"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def monte_carlo_qber_with_eve(num_trials=500, key_length=5000, bins=30):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Run Monte Carlo simulation to analyze QBER distribution with Eve present.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Parameters:\n",
    "    num_trials (int): Number of simulation trials\n",
    "    key_length (int): Number of bits per trial\n",
    "    bins (int): Number of histogram bins\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "    dict: Simulation results and statistics\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    qbers = []\n",
    "    detections = 0\n",
    "\n",
    "    print(\"\\nRunning Monte Carlo simulation...\")\n",
    "    start_time = time.time()\n",
    "\n",
    "    for _ in range(num_trials):\n",
    "        alice_bits, alice_bases, bob_bases, eve_base_inc, eve_base_tran = random_with_eve(key_length)\n",
    "        bob_bits, eve_bits = simulation_with_eve(alice_bases, alice_bits, bob_bases, eve_base_inc, eve_base_tran)\n",
    "        qber = compute_qber(alice_bases, bob_bases, alice_bits, bob_bits)\n",
    "        qbers.append(qber)\n",
    "\n",
    "        if qber >= 0.05:  # Eve detection threshold\n",
    "            detections += 1\n",
    "\n",
    "    end_time = time.time()\n",
    "    runtime = end_time - start_time\n",
    "\n",
    "    mean_qber = np.mean(qbers)\n",
    "    std_qber = np.std(qbers)\n",
    "    detection_probability = detections / num_trials\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Print summary\n",
    "    print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*50)\n",
    "    print(\"Monte Carlo BB84 with Eve - QBER Summary\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Trials: {num_trials}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Bits per trial: {key_length}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Mean QBER: {mean_qber:.4f}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Standard Deviation: {std_qber:.4f}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Eve detected in {detections}/{num_trials} trials\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Detection Probability: {detection_probability:.3f}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Runtime: {runtime:.2f} seconds\")\n",
    "    print(\"=\"*50)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Plot histogram with fits\n",
    "    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "    plt.hist(qbers, bins=bins, density=True, alpha=0.6, color='blue', label='QBER Histogram')\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Binomial distribution fit\n",
    "    N = int(key_length / 2)  # approx number of matched bits\n",
    "    p = mean_qber\n",
    "    k_vals = np.arange(0, N+1)\n",
    "    q_vals = k_vals / N\n",
    "    pmf_vals = binom.pmf(k_vals, N, p)\n",
    "    pdf_scaled = pmf_vals / (q_vals[1] - q_vals[0])  # scale to density\n",
    "    plt.plot(q_vals, pdf_scaled, 'r--', linewidth=2, label='Binomial Fit')\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Gaussian fit\n",
    "    x = np.linspace(0, 1, 200)\n",
    "    plt.plot(x, norm.pdf(x, mean_qber, std_qber), 'g-.', label='Gaussian Fit')\n",
    "\n",
    "    plt.xlabel('QBER')\n",
    "    plt.ylabel('Probability Density')\n",
    "    plt.title('BB84 QBER Distribution with Eve (Binomial and Gaussian Fits)')\n",
    "    plt.legend()\n",
    "    plt.grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n",
    "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "    return {\n",
    "        'qbers': qbers,\n",
    "        'mean_qber': mean_qber,\n",
    "        'std_qber': std_qber,\n",
    "        'detection_probability': detection_probability,\n",
    "        'runtime': runtime\n",
    "    }"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The above code simulates the Monte-Carlo BB84 protocol with Eve for a specific number of bits and trials in order to create a binomial distribution plot of\n",
    "the QBER probability. This allowed us to compare results for a range of different bit lengths and trial number, clearly showing the binomial tending towards\n",
    "a Gaussian with larger number of trials (data becomes almost continuous at very large trial number, with an average QBER = 0.25). An example is shown below for\n",
    " 1000 trial runs\n",
